Last night I was in Paris, in a theatre amongst the fashion elite, watching @olivier_rousteing documentary film, WonderBoy

I’ve been in this industry for many years but last night was the first time I felt like I kinda fit in....Not because of confidence in what I have contributed to this industry, but because of the normalcy of content I was watching on screen.... Olivier bravely let the curtain down and made a filter free film about the most vulnerable parts of his life......and it’s Fkn Brilliant!

When I saw his grandparent’s humble home, I saw my grandmothers kitchen where my whole family would congregate..... When I saw his relationship with his parents, 2 hard working people who are probably clueless to the reality of this fashion/entertainment world,  I saw mine as well...... Who woulda thought the chicest, most talented boy wonder of fashion, would come from a home that had  a BarcaLounger?(which looked like was his fave at his grandparents house.) The film shows so much of his insanely brilliant designs, ridic amounts of a-list celebrity, and prime BTS of the beau monde of fashion, but the most beautiful scenes in his film occur in the most basic of places.  The kind of places I come from...(and the majority of people reading.....) Oliviers story is as complicated as it is familiar to everyone who sees his film. 
Watch the Film. Olivier is WonderBoy.  His film is a gift to all those with challenged lives or those who think impossible is all that’s possible. WonderBoy is a call to find the wonder in your life.  Olivier is living proof that wonder doesn’t discriminate, it only goes to those willing to fight for it!  Thank You Olivier, Thank you for letting us into your world!  Your creative genius doesn’t hold a candle to your generous heart & all the love you give!!! U know I Love u!  SwipeTilTheEndForSomeEpicChoreo;)
